        "description": "<blockquote>\n<p>\n        <strong>Show, Hide, Close WP Comments</strong>\n    </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This plugin allows you to disable, enable or close WordPress comments on post types, pages etc. You can also hide main comments menu and admin bar menu for comments.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>You May Also Like</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\n    <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/gs-facebook-comments/\" rel=\"ugc\">WP Social Comments</a> | <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-instagram-post/\" rel=\"ugc\">WP Social Post and Widget </a>| <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woosocio/\" rel=\"ugc\">WooSocio</a> | <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wootweet/\" rel=\"ugc\">WP Twitter Post (WooTweet)</a>\n  </p>\n</blockquote>\n",
        "installation": "<p>Here are few steps to follow:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>disable-wp-comments</code> folder to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Select Disable Comments page from wordpress menu for settings.</li>\n<li>Select post types to applay options for comments settings.</li>\n<li>That&#8217;s it. You&#8217;re ready to go!</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='can%20i%20restore%20comments%20after%20disabling%20them%3F'>\nCan I restore comments after disabling them?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes you can resotre, show WordPress comments anytime you want. Just set options for that.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id='can%20i%20re%20open%20comments%20after%20closing%20them%3F'>\nCan I re open comments after closing them?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes you can re open WordPress comments anytime you want. Just see options for that.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.1.1 &#8211; 08/02/2023</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: Quality check done.</li>\n<li>Fix:    Minor bugs fixed.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1 &#8211; 27/10/2020</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New:    Disable Gutenberg Comments block.</li>\n<li>Update: Compatible with 2020 theme.</li>\n<li>Fix:    Bugs fixed.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0 &#8211; 12/12/2019</h4>\n<p>First release.</p>\n"
